                    "company": "Energy For One World",
                    "description": "Energy For One World (EFOW) is a boutique consulting firm focused on organizing the delivery of Sustainable Energy-Economy Architectures and UN Sustainable Developments into Sustainable Societies. \n\nGiven the realities we are today in (e.g. Ukraine War), our year 2023 theme and focus is: \n\nHow are we doing Halfway 2030?\n\n\"In the beginner's mind there are many possibilities,\nbut in the expert's there are few.\"-\u00a0Shunryu Suzuki (1905-1971)\n\nIn very simple terms- one could state that we \u2013the energy sector-\u00a0we have the following three and common goals:\n\n- Support the UN Sustainable Development Goals.\n- Implement the Paris Agreement.\n- Help build Sustainable Societies\n\nwhereby Energy is further closely linked to the Geo-politics of Emotions, Security and not the least our Economies, Ecology and Societies.\n\nHow can we best support and/or improve the present international working approaches and policies towards Energy, Climate Change and the UN SDGs-, and whereby our goal is to realize :\n\nEnergy, Societies and Economies Free of Concerns. Here and There. Now and tomorrow?\n\nThe invitation is, and Halfway 2030, to see with open minds, to share in our awareness, find \u201cthe  tone of voice\u201d, the organisational \u201cforms and formats- the  bridges\" and \u201cperhaps see more simpler and direct ways to drive the human and corporate capacities and capabilities for deliveries\u201d\u00a0 and by which we can integrate corporate, national and civic interests, formulate the (energy-economy) programs- that makes some common sense.\u00a0 \n\nPerhaps, and at times, re-engineer the present \u201cinstitutionalized modes \u201d in the sector and into our ministries: to support a true step-change and transit towards new energy architectures- locally, regionally and internationally.\u00a0",
                    "title": "Founder & Director Energy For One World",
                    "employment_type": "Permanent"
                }
            ]
